Friday evening saw Education agency Unipass hold a cocktail party at the Anghiti Restaurant in Westlands, Nairobi. The aim of the agency is to provide more opportunities to talented Kenyan youth who may be hampered by the restrictions in the variety of courses offered and the limited number of university spots available in the country.Managing director Sanpreet Sehmiand executive directorMaureen Mutisya as well as Commission for University Education, senior assistant secretary Gilbert Opanga who emphasised the importance of licensing student recruitment agencies to counter unscrupulous factions. The cocktail also served to welcome members from 20 worldwide universities to Kenya on a recruitment drive.